A college student who was pushed out of a moving matatu on Thika Superhighway was buried on Saturday at Ndamene village in Imenti. The 21-year-old Doreen Mwiti died on June 13 after the incident involving a matatu belonging to Zamzam Sacco near Safari Park Hotel. Autopsy results showed she may have fallen head first and cracked her skull. Her arms also had bruises. Speaking during her burial, her sister Irene Ntinyari said they want justice. “We have lost a visionary. She was likeable. It is a big loss to us,” she said. Mwiti was pursuing a course in ICT at NIBs college. She was the fourth born in a family of seven. Mwiti died at the Neema Uhai Hospital.